Date: Wed 20 Mar 2013
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar> [edited]


Anthrax outbreak, Laprida, Province of Buenos Aires
---------------------------------------------------
This outbreak was identified on 15 Mar 2013 by the visiting veterinarian in a beef herd in the area of "Laguna Quillaluquen" in the Partido of Laprida, where 8 Angus yearlings which had died suddenly with blood extravasation from the natural openings. The herd consists of 156 head, which had not been vaccinated against anthrax.

The laboratory confirmed the diagnosis and the _Bacillus anthracis_ isolated was sensitive to penicillin, tetracycline, florfenicol, and ciprofloxacin, and resistant to trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole.

No farm staff were exposed to the pathogen and the carcasses will be disposed of in the standard manner by spraying them with formaldehyde and covering them with a thick plastic tarpaulin, pegged down along their edges.

--
Dr Ramon Noseda
CFO-Director/Microbiologist
